			<div class="content" id="post-content-2739924">
									

<p>In-universe, the SCP Foundation is a shadow organization with an abundance of professional scientist and researcher personnel. The reports written by these personnel should clearly indicate that <em>the writer knows what they're writing about</em>.</p>
<p>What if you're not a scientist? What if you don't have any research experience?</p>
<p>This is totally fine. It's just a matter of doing your fact-checking so you don't have obvious inaccuracies or inconsistencies happening in your article.</p>
<p>This forum is for <strong>assisting writers with researching material</strong> for their works, as well as <strong>discussing real-world science</strong> in relation to the SCP article writing process.</p>
<p>The main difference between this forum and the other Writing Help sections is that all of these discussions are open-ended, and are considered effectively ongoing indefinitely (as opposed to a question/answer thread or idea/draft thread that is finished when the author progresses to the next step of the writing process).</p>

							</div>

								
					
