<li>Celtic deities and monuments</li>
<li>Intestinal parasites and digestive disorders</li>
<li>Cellular respiration (digestion/food energy)</li>
<li>Human and <a href="http://journals.sagepub.com/doi/pdf/10.1258/002367777780959175">lab animal (pdf)</a> dietary requirements (and typical weights)</li>
<li>Lab animal breeds (including gene knockouts) and research methods</li>
<li>Mitochondria and the symptoms and genetics of mitochondrial disorders</li>
<li>Common chemical reagents</li>
<li>Alcohol poisoning</li>
<li>Bio Safety Levels</li>
<li>British geography</li>
<li>The circulatory system</li>
<li>Rabbit behaviour</li>
<li>The use of animal fats for biofuel</li>
</ul>
<p>And that's just the stuff I <em>used</em>.</p>

